name: r-classint
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.4-7" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-classint
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/classInt_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/classInt/classInt_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: a30e3a8987ce133944897100ab5bdc31b019d897969c452c3795f50ac234606e

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}  # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - r-kernsmooth               # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - r-class                    # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - r-e1071                    # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - {{ compiler('c') }}              # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ compiler('fortran') }}        # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_fortran') }}  # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-kernsmooth
    - r-class
    - r-e1071
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{ native }}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-kernsmooth
    - r-class
    - r-e1071

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('classInt')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('classInt')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/r-spatial/classInt/
  license: GPL-2.0-or-later
  summary: Selected commonly used methods for choosing univariate class intervals for mapping or other graphics purposes.
  license_family: GPL2
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - ocefpaf


# Package: classInt
# Version: 0.4-1
# Date: 2019-07-22
# Title: Choose Univariate Class Intervals
